Wash and dry all produce. Take out @butter{2%tbsp} and let sit at room temperature. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating greens and whites. Split @ciabatta bread{1} in half. Place @black peppercorns{1%tablespoon} in a #zip-close bag{}; crush in bag using a #rolling pin{} or a #heavy-bottomed pan{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @broccoli florets{8%oz} and 3 TBSP water. Cover pan and let steam until broccoli is bright green and just starting to become tender, about ~{3%minutes}. Uncover and allow remaining water to evaporate.

Toss a large drizzle of oil and half the garlic into pan with broccoli. Cook until broccoli is crisped and garlic is fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside. Carefully wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @ranch steak{10%oz} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season with plenty of salt and pepper. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Set aside to rest. Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and ¼ tsp crushed peppercorns (use more or less to taste). Cook until softened and fragrant, about ~{2%minutes}.

Stir @beef stock concentrate{1} and @dijon mustard{2%teaspoon} and ¼ cup water into pan, scraping up any browned bits on bottom. Let simmer until reduced by half, about ~{2%minutes}. Remove pan from heat, then stir in another @butter{1%tbsp}. Pour mixture into a #medium bowl{} and whisk in @sour cream{2%tablespoon}. Set aside. Mix together reserved 2 TBSP butter and remaining garlic in a #small bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread garlic butter onto cut sides of ciabatta. Heat pan used for broccoli over medium-high heat. Add ciabatta buttered-side down and toast until light golden, about ~{2-3%minutes}. Thinly slice steak against the grain. Divide between plates and spoon sauce over top. Sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve with broccoli and ciabatta on the side.